sect1.para:
The rate of photoionization is  \[
        \hbox{photoionization rate} = 
        \frac{B_\nu 4\pi d\nu}{h\nu} n_0\sigma _{bf}\overbrace{\left(1-{g_0\over g_+}{n_+\over n_0}\right)}^{
        {
        {\hbox{correction for}\atop\hbox{stimulated}}
        \atop\hbox{recombination}}
        }
\] where $n_0$ is the number density of neutrals. This has units of a number flux. The cross section $\sigma_{bf}$ depends on $\nu$ and $n_+/n_0$ is evaluated at the relative velocity $v$ such that $h\nu =\frac12m_e v^2 + \chi$, where $\chi$ is the threshold ionization energy.
